data.description:
Write a function that reformats the ` unstructuredArr ` to a more readible format. 
The returned value should be a nested object where the timestamps are the keys. Look at the example for clarification.

If the 'master' or 'slave' value is not present, set the value to ` null `

This is the data that will passed. The structure will always be the same, but the length of the array might change.

` unstructuredArr ` passed as argument through `dataMassager`:

``` 
const unstructuredArr = [
  {
    'Events.timeStamp': 2019,
    'Actor.roles': '{/slave/}',
    'Actor.age': 22
  },
{
    'Events.timeStamp': 2019,
    'Actor.roles': '{/master/}',
    'Actor.age': 34
  },
  {
    'Events.timeStamp': 2020,
    'Actor.roles': '{/master/}',
    'Actor.age': 39
  }
 ]
```

expected return value:
```
const myStructuredObj = {
  2019: {
    slave: 22,
    master: 34
  },
  2020: {
    slave: null,
    master: 39
  }
}
```

Feel free to give feedback and I'll handle them asap. Contribution are more than welcome!
Good luck!
